---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import { TOOLS } from '../lib/tools';

const origin = Astro.site?.origin ?? 'https://netrecon.pages.dev';
const mcpUrl = `${origin}/api/mcp`;

const claudeDesktopSnippet = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "netrecon": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote", "${mcpUrl}"]
    }
  }
}`;

const cursorSnippet = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "netrecon": {
      "url": "${mcpUrl}"
    }
  }
}`;

const vscodeSnippet = `{
  "mcp": {
    "servers": {
      "netrecon": {
        "type": "http",
        "url": "${mcpUrl}"
      }
    }
  }
}`;

const curlExample = `curl -s ${mcpUrl} \\
  -H 'content-type: application/json' \\
  -d '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"tools/list"}'`;
---

<Layout
  title="netrecon - MCP server"
  description="netrecon exposes all 9 diagnostic tools over the Model Context Protocol. Plug it into Claude Desktop, Cursor, or any MCP-aware agent."
>
  <section class="mcp-hero">
    <div class="prompt mono">$ netrecon --mcp</div>
    <h1>Agent-ready network diagnostics.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      netrecon is a first-class MCP server. Connect Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code, or any MCP-aware client
      and call the same diagnostics you'd run interactively - from inside your agent's reasoning loop.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mcp-endpoint">
    <h2>Endpoint</h2>
    <p>Single <strong>Streamable HTTP</strong> endpoint. No auth. No install. Stateless.</p>
    <pre class="mono code-block"><code>{mcpUrl}</code></pre>
    <p class="subtle">
      Rate-limited to 20 requests/minute/IP. The underlying tools are SSRF-guarded
      (<a href="/about">see security doc</a>).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mcp-clients">
    <h2>Client setup</h2>

    <details open>
      <summary><strong>Claude Desktop</strong> <span class="subtle">(stdio bridge via <code>mcp-remote</code>)</span></summary>
      <p>Add to <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code> (macOS) or <code>%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json</code> (Windows):</p>
      <pre class="mono code-block"><code>{claudeDesktopSnippet}</code></pre>
      <p class="subtle">Claude Desktop speaks stdio; <code>mcp-remote</code> bridges stdio &harr; HTTP. Restart Claude after editing.</p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary><strong>Cursor</strong> <span class="subtle">(native Streamable HTTP)</span></summary>
      <p>Add to <code>~/.cursor/mcp.json</code>:</p>
      <pre class="mono code-block"><code>{cursorSnippet}</code></pre>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary><strong>VS Code / Continue / other HTTP-native clients</strong></summary>
      <pre class="mono code-block"><code>{vscodeSnippet}</code></pre>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary><strong>Raw JSON-RPC</strong> <span class="subtle">(curl)</span></summary>
      <pre class="mono code-block"><code>{curlExample}</code></pre>
    </details>
  </section>

  <section class="mcp-tools">
    <h2>Available tools</h2>
    <p>These are the exact same tool definitions behind the UI and the JSON API. <code>tools/list</code> returns the same set.</p>
    <table class="tools-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Tool</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {TOOLS.map((t) => (
          <tr>
            <td><code>{t.name}</code></td>
            <td>{t.description}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="mcp-notes">
    <h2>Notes for agent authors</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Start with <code>analyze</code></strong> for most investigations - it runs the full correlated pipeline and returns <code>summary.findings</code> + <code>summary.nextCommands</code> suitable for direct reasoning.</li>
      <li>Tool results return both <code>structuredContent</code> (machine-readable) and a <code>content[0].text</code> compact-JSON fallback for clients that only read text.</li>
      <li>The server is <strong>stateless</strong>: <code>initialize</code> establishes a protocol version but issues no session. You can batch requests freely.</li>
      <li>Large outputs: a full <code>analyze</code> report can be 50-200KB. Point your agent at <code>summary</code> first, drill into sub-reports on demand.</li>
      <li>Protocol versions supported: <code>2025-06-18</code> (preferred), <code>2025-03-26</code>, <code>2024-11-05</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .mcp-hero { padding: 2rem 0 1rem; }
  .mcp-hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem; }
  .mcp-hero .tagline { color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 60ch; }
  .mcp-endpoint, .mcp-clients, .mcp-tools, .mcp-notes { margin: 2rem 0; }
  .mcp-endpoint h2, .mcp-clients h2, .mcp-tools h2, .mcp-notes h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--fg-muted); margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  .code-block {
    background: var(--bg-subtle, #0d1117);
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #1f2933);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .mcp-clients details {
    border: 1px solid var(--border, #1f2933);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.7rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
    background: var(--bg-card, #0c1117);
  }
  .mcp-clients details[open] { padding-bottom: 1rem; }
  .mcp-clients summary { cursor: pointer; padding: 0.2rem 0; }
  .mcp-clients summary code { font-size: 0.85em; }
  .mcp-clients p { margin: 0.6rem 0; }
  .subtle { color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.9em; }
  .tools-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .tools-table th, .tools-table td {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border, #1f2933);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.5rem;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .tools-table th { color: var(--fg-muted); font-weight: 500; }
  .tools-table td:first-child { white-space: nowrap; }
  .tools-table td code { color: var(--accent, #5cd2a3); }
  .mcp-notes ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
